<plot>A calm and quiet Sunday morning -- three hard working farmers, two of Hawaiian descent and one Japanese, take a walk in the forest, talk story about their families, their crops, and the homeland -- a routine that they have been doing for quite some time. However, this is no ordinary Sunday, for this is a day that will live in infamy: December 7, 1941.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?521579</url></doc>
